"title": "Colors",
"content": "My name is Adam. I am in my classroom with my friends Ali and Sarah. Today, our teacher Ms. Lana teaches us about colors. Ms. Lana says, 'Good morning, everyone! Today we learn about colors.' She holds up a red apple and asks, 'What color is this?' Ali says, 'It is red!' Ms. Lana smiles. 'Very good, Ali! Red.' She writes 'red' on the board. Then she holds up a blue book. 'What color is this?' Sarah says, 'It is blue!' Ms. Lana says, 'Yes, Sarah! Blue.' She writes 'blue' on the board. Next, she points to a yellow pencil on her desk. 'And this pencil? What color is it?' I say, 'It is yellow!' Ms. Lana nods. 'Good job, Adam! Yellow.' She writes 'yellow' on the board. Ms. Lana shows us a green leaf. 'This is a leaf. What color is it?' We all say together, 'Green!' Ms. Lana writes 'green' on the board. Then she holds up an orange fruit. 'And this orange? What color is it?' Ali laughs. 'It is orange!' Ms. Lana says, 'Yes! The fruit and the color have the same name. Orange.' She shows us a purple flower. 'This flower is purple.' Sarah repeats, 'Purple.' Ms. Lana shows us a pink eraser. 'This eraser is pink.' I say, 'Pink.' Ms. Lana shows us a brown desk. 'Our desks are brown.' We all look at our desks. They are brown. Ms. Lana points to her black hair. 'My hair is black.' Then she points to the white board. 'The board is white.' She writes all the colors on the board: red, blue, yellow, green, orange, purple, pink, brown, black, white. Ms. Lana says, 'Now let's play a game. I say a color, and you point to something in the room with that color. Ready?' We say, 'Ready!' Ms. Lana says, 'Red!' Ali points to his red backpack. Sarah points to a red flower on her desk. I point to a red mark on my book. Ms. Lana says, 'Blue!' I point to the blue sky outside the window. Ali points to his blue shirt. Sarah points to a blue pen. Ms. Lana says, 'Green!' We all point to the green plants near the window. Ms. Lana claps. 'Very good, everyone! You know your colors well.' At the end of the lesson, Ms. Lana gives us paper and crayons. She says, 'Draw a picture and use all the colors we learn today. Use red, blue, yellow, green, orange, purple, pink, brown, black, and white.' We start drawing. I draw a house with a brown door, a red roof, and green grass. The sky is blue and the sun is yellow. Sarah draws a garden with many purple and pink flowers. Ali draws a big orange cat. We are happy. Colors are fun!",
