"content": "Many people think that being smart (IQ) is the only way to be successful. But psychologists say that Emotional Intelligence (EQ) is also very important. EQ is the ability to understand your own feelings and the feelings of others. There are four parts to EQ: knowing yourself, managing your emotions, understanding others, and building good relationships. For example, if you are angry, a person with high EQ will stay calm and not shout. In a job, a leader who understands people's feelings can motivate the team better. The good news is that you can improve your EQ by practicing and being a good listener. Understanding your emotions helps you feel happier and less stressed.",
